04/03/2007
WASHINGTON, United States -- Bulgarian Economy and Energy Minister Rumen Ovcharov says a pair of leading US companies are interested in investment opportunities in Bulgaria. 
Midway through a two week working visit to the US, Ovcharov said on Friday (March 2nd) that both ITT and LockheÐµd Martin are interested in programmes to modernise the Bulgarian army and the defence industry. 
ITT has also expressed interest in potential investments in water and waste management projects and the production of radio telecommunication equipment. 
(24 Chasa - 03/03/07; Bulgarian Government website, Mediapool - 02/03/07)
